library(tidyverse)
precinct_results <- tibble()

AK

Alaska has just one district

ak <- read_csv("vtd_data/2020_VTD/AK/2020_election_AK.csv") %>%
  summarize(y2020 = sum(D_2020_pres)/(sum(D_2020_pres) + sum(R_2020_pres)),
            y2018 = sum(D_2018_gov)/(sum(D_2018_gov) + sum(R_2018_gov)),
            y2016 = sum(D_2016_pres)/(sum(D_2016_pres) + sum(R_2016_pres))) %>%
  select(y2020, y2018, y2016) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(y2020, y2018, y2016), names_to = "year", values_to = "dem_2p") %>%
  mutate(District = "AL") %>%
  mutate(state = "AK")
Rows: 456 Columns: 16 Column specification 
Delimiter: ","
chr  (1): GEOID20
dbl (15): Tot_2020_sen, D_2020_sen, R_2020_sen, Tot_2020_pres, D_2020_pres, R_2020_pres, Tot_2018_gov, D_2018_gov,...
 Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
 Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
precinct_results <- rbind(precinct_results, ak)

AL

al <- read_csv("vtd_data/2020_VTD/AL/2020_election_AL.csv") %>%
  select(GEOID20, D_2020_pres, R_2020_pres, D_2018_gov, R_2018_gov, D_2016_pres, R_2016_pres) %>%
  left_join(read_csv("precinct/precinct-al.csv"), by = "GEOID20") %>%
  drop_na(District) %>%
  group_by(District) %>%
  summarize(y2020 = sum(D_2020_pres)/(sum(D_2020_pres) + sum(R_2020_pres)),
            y2018 = sum(D_2018_gov)/(sum(D_2018_gov) + sum(R_2018_gov)),
            y2016 = sum(D_2016_pres)/(sum(D_2016_pres) + sum(R_2016_pres))) %>%
  pivot_longer(!District, names_to = "year", values_to = "dem_2p") %>%
  mutate(state = "AL")
